abstract: Michael Bloomberg faced a barrage of attacks at his first Democratic presidential debate on Wednesday, as his rivals rushed to criticize the billionaire businessman for his wealth, record on race and history of sexist comments.

abstract: Terry Reece has long been skeptical that voters would back Bernie Sanders, a 78-year-old self-described democratic socialist who is just months removed from a heart attack. Then the Vermont senator essentially tied for first place in the Democratic Party's Iowa caucuses and won its New Hampshire primary.

lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Terry Reece has long been skeptical that voters would back Bernie Sanders, a 78-year-old self-described democratic socialist who is just months removed from a heart attack. Then the Vermont senator essentially tied for first place in the Democratic Party's Iowa caucuses and won its New Hampshire primary.

abstract: From the opening bell, Democrats savaged New York billionaire Mike Bloomberg and raised pointed questions about Bernie Sanders' take-no-prisoners politics during a contentious debate Wednesday night that threatened to further muddy the party's urgent quest to defeat President Donald Trump.

abstract: Mike Bloomberg will confront the greatest test of his presidential campaign on Wednesday when he faces five Democratic rivals in a debate in Las Vegas that could fundamentally change the direction of the party’s 2020 nomination fight.

abstract: Bernie Sanders' presidential campaign plans to ask for a partial recount of the Iowa caucus results after the state Democratic Party released results of its recanvass late Tuesday that show Sanders and Pete Buttigieg in an effective tie.
snippet: Bernie Sanders' presidential campaign plans to ask for a partial recount of the Iowa caucus results after the state Democratic Party released results of its recanvass late Tuesday that show Sanders and Pete Buttigieg in an effective tie.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Bernie Sanders' presidential campaign plans to ask for a partial recount of the Iowa caucus results after the state Democratic Party released results of its recanvass late Tuesday that show Sanders and Pete Buttigieg in an effective tie.

abstract: Japan's government is expected to maintain its assessment that the economy is recovering in a monthly report due on Thursday, two sources familiar with its thinking said, despite the widening fallout from the coronavirus outbreak.
snippet: Japan's government is expected to maintain its assessment that the economy is recovering in a monthly report due on Thursday, two sources familiar with its thinking said, despite the widening fallout from the coronavirus outbreak.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Japan's government is expected to maintain its assessment that the economy is recovering in a monthly report due on Thursday, two sources familiar with its thinking said, despite the widening fallout from the coronavirus outbreak.
headline_main: Japan Government to Keep View Economy Recovering Despite Virus Risk: Sources
headline_print_headline: Japan Government to Keep View Economy Recovering Despite Virus Risk: Sources
